header.gameNote: LAS VEGAS INVITATIONAL AT LAS VEGAS

article.headline: Tennessee St. 69, Morgan St. 64
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Robert Covington scored 23 points to lead Tennessee State over Morgan State 69-64 on Saturday in the final round of the Las Vegas Invitational. Patrick Miller added 15 points and Kellen Thornton 12 for the Tigers (3-4). Covington had eight rebounds and three blocks. Kevin Thompson led the Bears (0-6) with 16 points. Jordan Cyphers' 3-pointer from the left corner with 1:17 left gave Tennessee State the lead for good at 63-61 after six lead changes and seven ties. The Bears, who led for most of the second half, had a 45-37 advantage with 11:59 left before Tennessee State took over. The Bears built a 19-8 first-half lead, but the Tigers responded with a 17-4 run and led 30-28 at halftime. Tennessee State shot 9 of 16 from 3-point range.
